data.meta_description: Warner Baxter. 2nd Actor to win the Academy Awards' Best Actor Oscar (for his role in Old Arizona). Baxter was an American actor who started his movie career in silent movies. Baxter's most notable silent films are probably The Great Gatsby (1926) and The Awful Truth (1925). When talkies came out, Baxter became even more famous. Baxter's most notable talkies are In Old Arizona (1929), 42nd Street (1932), Slave Ship (1937), Kidnapped (1938) and The Slippery Pearls.
